Package com.intellij.openapi.roots.libraries

Class LibraryType<P extends LibraryProperties>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.roots.libraries.LibraryPresentationProvider<P>
      • com.intellij.openapi.roots.libraries.LibraryType<P>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DownloadableLibraryType, PythonLibraryType, RepositoryLibraryType, UnknownLibraryType

    public abstract class LibraryType<P extends LibraryProperties>
extends LibraryPresentationProvider<P>
    Override this class to provide custom library type. Type and properties for custom libraries are stored in project configuration files. If they can be detected automatically it's better to use LibraryPresentationProvider extension point instead.
    The implementation should be registered in plugin.xml:

    <extensions defaultExtensionNs="com.intellij">
      <library.type implementation="qualified-class-name"/>
    </extensions>

    See Also:
    LibraryPresentationProvider
